  <li>
    <p>Antidepressants have failed to provide an effective remedy for cases of depression in the western world.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>SSRIs and other antidepressants prescription has increased from less than 10 million in 1991 to almost 40 million in 2009.</p>
  </li>
</ul>

<p>These levels of prescribing have not been associated with a reduction in the related burden of care, with the number of people claiming incapacity benefit for a mental or behavioural disorder rising steadily from under 750 000 in 2000 to nearly a million in 2008.</p>
